Senator Dick Durbin, the Assistant Senate Majority Leader, released a statement supporting President Obama's American Jobs Act. Durbin praises the plan for creating new jobs for teachers, veterans, and construction workers. He highlights that the plan also includes tax cuts for small businesses and middle-class families, as well as tax credits for companies that hire new workers. Durbin emphasizes the importance of setting aside partisanship and working together to address the issue of unemployment. He describes the plan as good, fair, and fully paid for, noting that many of the proposals have received bipartisan support in the past.